<H2><A NAME="SECTION00014000000000000000">
Description</A>
</H2>A freeze counter is an enabled counter which holds its final value (regardless of enables) until it is reset. Thus, a <SPAN CLASS="MATH"><IMG
 WIDTH="19" HEIGHT="16" ALIGN="BOTTOM" BORDER="0"
 SRC="img4.png"
 ALT="$2^5$"></SPAN> freeze counter will count from 0 to 31 on 31 enables, but will hold 31 thereafter until a reset occurs. This block is useful for writing data in a single pass to memory without looping. 

